## Conditional routing (signal → next policy)

> **Invariant 0 — routing is additive, never subtractive.** These signals *suggest*
> the next policy; they never hide or forbid reading any policy. This index is the
> hub and is always reachable, so no path dead-ends — if a predicate is false the edge
> is simply **bypassed**, not closed. A `block` applies only to a load-bearing *write*
> (e.g. writing phenotype code before its timeline exists), never to *consulting* a
> policy. When unsure whether a relevant policy sits off the obvious path, run
> `/coverage`. The machine-readable mirror of this table is
> `.claude/policy/routing.yml` (read by the `policy_router` hook).

Read each edge as: **at** the *From* policy, **if** the *Signal* holds, **go to** the
*Next* policy; otherwise bypass.

| From | Signal (predicate) | → Next | Bypass when |
|------|--------------------|--------|-------------|
| `analysis/data-onboarding.md` | repeated-measures / longitudinal structure | `analysis/longitudinal-data.md` | cross-sectional (one row per subject) |
| `analysis/initial-data-analysis.md` | ready to model | `analysis/regression-modeling.md`, `analysis/model-assumptions.md` | description-only |
| `analysis/regression-modeling.md` | clustered / repeated dependence | `analysis/correlated-data.md` | independent observations |
| `analysis/correlated-data.md` | estimand subject-specific **or** MAR-dropout continuous | `analysis/longitudinal-data.md` (MMRM) | estimand marginal/population-average → GLS/GEE here |
| `analysis/longitudinal-data.md` | MAR dropout to handle | `analysis/missingness.md` (MMRM / MI) | MCAR + negligible loss → complete-case |
| `analysis/pseudocode-first.md` | complex multi-step logic | `analysis/incremental-functions.md` → `analysis/code-style.md` | trivial one-liner → inline |
{% if 'causal' in modules %}| `analysis/data-onboarding.md` | observational, **non-routine** design (primary cohort/RCT) | `docs/analysis/modules/causal.md` | routinely-collected/EHR source → use the health chain below, **not** causal-from-scratch |
{% endif %}{% if project_profile == 'health-data' %}
**Health-data edges** (clinical codes / EHR / claims):

| From | Signal (predicate) | → Next | Bypass when |
|------|--------------------|--------|-------------|
| `analysis/data-onboarding.md`, `health/secondary-data.md` | clinical codes present (ICD / SNOMED / RxNorm / ATC / CPT / LOINC) | `health/code-mapping.md` | no coded clinical fields → stay in the analysis layer |
